According to Section 1006.2.1(a) of the Florida Building Code: Two exits are required when either (i) the design occupant load exceeds 30 and common path of egress travel distance is more than 75 feet, or both conditions apply; (ii) there's an absence of a sprinkler system in accordance with Section 903.2.4(a), as per Table 1006.2.

Section 1006.2.1(b)(i-iii): Exceptions to the requirement for two exits or exit access doorways from a single space include: (I) Care suites in Group I-2 occupancies that comply with Section 407.4, and similar exceptions;

However, note that these exceptions depend on specific conditions detailed in each of those referenced sections which are not provided here directly within the context text.
